public static final class LocationEntry
    implements BaseColumns {
    psf String TABLE_NAME = "location";
    psf String COLUMN_COORD_LAT = "latitude";
    psf String COLUMN_COORD_LON = "longitude";
    psf String COLUMN_CITY_NAME = "city_name";
    psf String COLUMN_LOC_SETTING
        = "column_location_setting";
}

sqLiteDatabase.execSQL("CREATE TABLE "
  + LocationEntry.TABLE_NAME
  + " ("
  + LocationEntry._ID
  + " INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, "
  + LocationEntry.COLUMN_COORDINATE_LATITUDE
  + " REAL NOT NULL, "
  + LocationEntry.COLUMN_COORDINATE_LONGITUDE
  + " REAL NOT NULL, "
  + LocationEntry.COLUMN_CITY_NAME
  + " TEXT NOT NULL, "
  + LocationEntry.COLUMN_LOCATION_SETTING
  + " TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL "
  + " );"
);

Test with sqlite3 
beforehand

  = new WeatherDbHelper(mContext)

  = createNorthPoleLocationValues();
long insertedId = writableDb
  .insert(
    LocationEntry.TABLE_NAME,
    null,
    northPoleContentValues);
assertTrue("invalid database id",
  insertedId != -1);

validateCurrentRecord("differ",

insertedCursor.close();
writableDb.close();
